contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

02:12.967 --> 02:15.967
[siren wailing]

02:17.800 --> 02:18.832
[car horn honking]

02:18.833 --> 02:21.867
Hmm!
[sighs]

02:24.233 --> 02:27.267
Oh, sheesh.

02:31.267 --> 02:32.700
Oh.

02:42.433 --> 02:43.599
Oh! Whoa!

02:43.600 --> 02:45.433
Sorry, buddy.

02:47.833 --> 02:49.733
Ah...

02:52.433 --> 02:55.400
[shower running]

03:07.033 --> 03:09.232
Hey.

03:09.233 --> 03:10.866
Where you been?

03:10.867 --> 03:13.800
I got you somethin'.

03:15.933 --> 03:17.366
Mmm...

03:17.367 --> 03:18.832
I was tired.

03:18.833 --> 03:21.200
Slept in the truck awhile.

03:24.767 --> 03:26.299
How'd you sleep?

03:26.300 --> 03:28.632
Like a bear...

03:28.633 --> 03:30.199
with a spring up his ass.

03:30.200 --> 03:32.166
[sighs]
- Whoo!

03:32.167 --> 03:33.866
Could you--
could you get dressed, man?

03:33.867 --> 03:35.232
Put--put some clothes on?

03:35.233 --> 03:36.532
Why? You excited?

03:36.533 --> 03:38.432
No, I want to be out of here

03:38.433 --> 03:40.199
before the Sunshine Band wakes up.

03:40.200 --> 03:41.566
We quittin'?

03:41.567 --> 03:44.100
No, we--we got
a bridge to find.

03:47.733 --> 03:49.332
<i>♪ ♪</i>

03:49.333 --> 03:52.332
<i>Yes!
[chuckles]</i>

03:52.333 --> 03:54.999
Oh, hey.

03:55.000 --> 03:56.566
Y'all going somewhere?

03:56.567 --> 03:58.266
Doing what we came here to do,

03:58.267 --> 03:59.799
find that bridge.

03:59.800 --> 04:03.766
Good, good.
Take Chub and Paco with you.

04:03.767 --> 04:05.799
- No.
- We're good.

04:05.800 --> 04:07.232
Glad to hear it.

04:07.233 --> 04:09.099
Just let these boys
get cleaned up.

04:09.100 --> 04:11.666
And, uh, oh, had a great run.

04:11.667 --> 04:14.732
Morning ritual, you know,
you got to stay in shape.

04:14.733 --> 04:16.565
I want some breakfast.

04:16.567 --> 04:18.899
Yeah, Trudy's
gonna make some eggs

04:18.899 --> 04:20.298
before you head out.

04:20.300 --> 04:22.399
That girl can cook.

04:22.400 --> 04:23.932
Right, Hap?

04:23.933 --> 04:27.132
Bad joke.
I couldn't resist.

04:27.133 --> 04:29.799
[chuckles]
You know, we don't have

04:29.800 --> 04:31.599
room in here
for four, so--

04:31.600 --> 04:33.232
Oh, hey, well, take the van.

04:33.233 --> 04:35.267
Plenty of room.

04:42.800 --> 04:44.466
I'm telling you right now--

04:44.467 --> 04:46.366
that thing got a mattress
and beaded curtains,

04:46.367 --> 04:47.766
I'm walkin'.

04:47.767 --> 04:50.233
[engine rumbling]

04:51.667 --> 04:52.932
What do we got here?

04:52.933 --> 04:54.499
Hell if I know.

04:54.500 --> 04:56.566
[grunts]

04:56.567 --> 04:58.499
[muttering indistinctly]

04:58.500 --> 04:59.966
Glorious morning.

04:59.967 --> 05:02.466
Heavens are tellin'
of the glory of God.

05:02.467 --> 05:05.099
Their expanse is declaring
the work of His hands.

05:05.100 --> 05:06.532
Meaning?

05:06.533 --> 05:08.332
- Meaning he's the Creator.
- Oh.

05:08.333 --> 05:09.899
And he's watching us...

05:09.900 --> 05:11.032
right now.

05:11.033 --> 05:12.566
Hap, you see anybody?

05:12.567 --> 05:14.432
- No.
- Oh...

05:14.433 --> 05:18.499
Just a cloud, and that looks
like Willie Nelson.

05:18.500 --> 05:21.032
Hey, you wouldn't happen
to be lost, now, would you?

05:21.033 --> 05:23.032
Just the opposite, brother.

05:23.033 --> 05:24.432
I saw your entrance

05:24.433 --> 05:27.832
and your, uh--
your lawn pieces,

05:27.833 --> 05:29.699
thought you might be
in need of the Holy Spirit.

05:29.700 --> 05:32.332
You blind?
See them signs?

05:32.333 --> 05:34.232
This is private property.

05:34.233 --> 05:36.232
How the hell did you
get past that gate?

05:36.233 --> 05:37.632
It--it was open.

05:37.633 --> 05:39.232
Afraid I didn't see
any signs, sir.

05:39.233 --> 05:40.832
Sorry.

05:40.833 --> 05:42.799
My name's Prescott Jones,

05:42.800 --> 05:44.732
and I sell the Lord's Word.

05:44.733 --> 05:46.166
We're atheists.

05:46.167 --> 05:47.466
Oh, well, too bad.

05:47.467 --> 05:49.666
But I'm running a sale, friend.

05:49.667 --> 05:51.566
You run it somewhere else.

05:51.567 --> 05:54.667
We're busy,
and I ain't your friend.

05:58.800 --> 06:01.499
Right you are.
Right you are.

06:01.500 --> 06:05.232
I'll just leave this here then.

06:05.233 --> 06:07.100
On the house.

06:11.067 --> 06:13.300
[engine turns over]

06:16.133 --> 06:18.300
<i>I hate Bible thumpers!</i>

06:24.133 --> 06:25.632
You left that gate
open, didn't you?

06:25.633 --> 06:27.200
Yeah, yeah.

06:28.433 --> 06:29.599
I won't tell if you won't.

06:29.600 --> 06:31.266
Oh, no.

06:31.267 --> 06:34.232
<i>[gentle music]</i>

06:34.233 --> 06:40.799
<i>♪ ♪</i>

06:40.800 --> 06:42.466
<i>Just stay straight.</i>

06:42.467 --> 06:44.599
Trail's not far.

06:44.600 --> 06:47.266
[police siren whooping]

06:47.267 --> 06:48.892
<i>[indistinct police radio
transmission]</i>

06:50.300 --> 06:51.733
Ah, shit.

06:56.100 --> 06:58.232
How about that way?

06:58.233 --> 06:59.433
Yeah, it winds around.

07:08.300 --> 07:10.499
Holy rollers, I get.

07:10.500 --> 07:12.532
But you got a problem
with the police too?

07:12.533 --> 07:15.832
Something we should know about?

07:15.833 --> 07:18.166
Did you ever hear
of the Mechanics?

07:18.167 --> 07:19.667
Paco was with them.

07:22.233 --> 07:25.366
Weren't they a splinter branch
of the Weathermen?

07:25.367 --> 07:27.499
Protested 'Nam, blew up buildings

07:27.500 --> 07:28.966
and recruitin' stations?

07:28.967 --> 07:30.566
People too, if I recall.

07:30.567 --> 07:33.167
Something like that.

07:44.800 --> 07:46.132
Well?

07:46.133 --> 07:47.932
It looks right,

07:47.933 --> 07:49.799
but it was a long time ago.

07:49.800 --> 07:51.466
I just followed my dad.

07:51.467 --> 07:52.866
I tell you...

07:52.867 --> 07:54.166
I don't like these two clowns

07:54.167 --> 07:55.632
breathing down my neck.

07:55.633 --> 07:57.066
Let's go.

07:57.067 --> 07:59.332
How hard can it be
to find a damn river?

07:59.333 --> 08:00.966
Well, you tell me.

08:00.967 --> 08:03.399
You and Howard couldn't find it.

08:03.400 --> 08:06.232
Well, you know so much.

08:06.233 --> 08:08.399
Which way?

08:08.400 --> 08:12.099
I'm pretty sure they both
lead down to the water, so...

08:12.100 --> 08:13.499
Pretty sure?

08:13.500 --> 08:14.699
Mm-hmm.

08:14.700 --> 08:16.199
We could take 'em both.

08:16.200 --> 08:17.866
[scoffs]

08:17.867 --> 08:19.499
That's the first
intelligent thing you've said.

08:19.500 --> 08:20.666
Meet you there.

08:20.667 --> 08:23.232
I don't think so.

08:23.233 --> 08:24.399
You want that hand, I suggest

08:24.400 --> 08:25.999
you keep it on a leash.

08:26.000 --> 08:27.599
[chuckles]

08:27.600 --> 08:29.699
You're with me, Hap.

08:29.700 --> 08:32.932
Who put you in charge?

08:32.933 --> 08:35.432
No way in hell
I'm going with Chub.

08:35.433 --> 08:36.933
You lead the way.

08:47.300 --> 08:51.999
<i>♪ ♪</i>

08:52.000 --> 08:55.099
So Trudy says you're a gay.

08:55.100 --> 08:57.599
What's that like?

08:57.600 --> 09:01.532
Let's try a version of this
where you don't talk.

09:01.533 --> 09:04.532
You don't act like any
homosexuals that I know of.

09:04.533 --> 09:06.366
You don't know any homosexuals.

09:06.367 --> 09:08.232
I'm just saying, it's just
rare to meet someone

09:08.233 --> 09:10.299
who's so comfortable
in their own skin.

09:10.300 --> 09:11.866
I mean, you're, like,

09:11.867 --> 09:13.633
the first gay black man
I've ever met.

09:16.400 --> 09:18.432
One more word,

09:18.433 --> 09:22.433
I'll be the last
gay black man you ever met.

09:26.467 --> 09:29.433
[wind howling]

09:37.267 --> 09:38.632
Leonard?

09:38.633 --> 09:41.633
[crow cawing]

09:44.100 --> 09:46.532
Leonard?

09:46.533 --> 09:48.166
Oh...

09:48.167 --> 09:49.333
Come on, Leonard.

09:50.500 --> 09:53.432
<i>Leonard!</i>

09:53.433 --> 09:55.099
<i>Tell me somethin'...</i>

09:55.100 --> 09:56.599
How does a man like you

09:56.600 --> 09:58.832
go from a group like the Mechanics

09:58.833 --> 10:00.966
to the Howard and Trudy show?

10:00.967 --> 10:04.666
What do you mean, a man like me?

10:04.667 --> 10:06.666
I know who you are.

10:06.667 --> 10:08.632
You weren't just a member
of the Mechanics.

10:08.633 --> 10:10.166
You were its leader--

10:10.167 --> 10:12.166
the bomb maker
who blew himself up.

10:12.167 --> 10:14.432
I was young.

10:14.433 --> 10:16.166
I stood up for somethin'.

10:16.167 --> 10:19.099
Blind faith and a cause, huh?

10:19.100 --> 10:22.232
Nobody said
it was gonna be easy.

10:22.233 --> 10:24.132
Some of us can stand the heat,

10:24.133 --> 10:26.732
and some of us can't.

10:26.733 --> 10:29.932
Besides, it ain't
that bad, this face.

10:29.933 --> 10:32.132
Only hurts when I smile.

10:32.133 --> 10:35.100
<i>[dogs barking,
men speaking indistinctly]</i>

10:39.367 --> 10:42.333
<i>[indistinct police radio
transmission]</i>

10:44.700 --> 10:47.666
Was this place always so popular?

10:47.667 --> 10:49.666
- Something about a dead cop.
- [gasps]

10:49.667 --> 10:53.299
Heard it back on the trail.

10:53.300 --> 10:55.466
Where's Chub?

10:55.467 --> 10:57.299
Long story.

10:57.300 --> 10:59.932
<i>[jaunty acoustic music]</i>

10:59.933 --> 11:02.699
All right, one, two...

11:02.700 --> 11:04.032
- Three.
- Three.

11:04.033 --> 11:05.566
[all grunting]

11:05.567 --> 11:07.999
Pull!

11:08.000 --> 11:09.566
[wailing]

11:09.567 --> 11:12.566
[vine snaps, all grunting]

11:12.567 --> 11:13.866
God damn it.

11:13.867 --> 11:17.032
<i>♪ ♪</i>

11:17.033 --> 11:18.432
Well, now what?

11:18.433 --> 11:20.966
We got some rope in the van.

11:20.967 --> 11:22.166
Yeah.

11:22.167 --> 11:28.799
<i>♪ ♪</i>

11:28.800 --> 11:31.199
- Good?
- Good.

11:31.200 --> 11:32.167
You ready, Chub?

11:32.168 --> 11:33.199
Yeah.

11:33.200 --> 11:35.699
One, two, three.

11:35.700 --> 11:36.999
Pull!

11:37.000 --> 11:38.999
All:
Pull!

11:39.000 --> 11:41.066
[mud splashing]

11:41.067 --> 11:43.666
Shit!

11:43.667 --> 11:45.699
[all sighing]

11:45.700 --> 11:48.366
[coughing]

11:48.367 --> 11:51.300
[all laughing]

11:56.033 --> 11:57.199
Where are your pants?

11:57.200 --> 12:00.632
[laughter]

12:00.633 --> 12:03.566
<i>[mellow country music playing]</i>

12:03.567 --> 12:05.566
<i>♪ ♪</i>

12:05.567 --> 12:07.932
Trudy, you got
customers waitin'.

12:07.933 --> 12:09.632
Table two.

12:09.633 --> 12:11.566
<i>♪ Looks like it's gonna be ♪</i>

12:11.567 --> 12:14.232
<i>♪ One of those days ♪</i>

12:14.233 --> 12:16.932
<i>♪ If this is your way
of getting me... ♪</i>

12:16.933 --> 12:19.799
Welcome to Family Burger,
where everyone's family.

12:19.800 --> 12:21.166
How can I help you?

12:21.167 --> 12:23.132
Family...

12:23.133 --> 12:24.499
Well, sister,

12:24.500 --> 12:25.899
you can let me
take you out dancing.

12:25.900 --> 12:27.332
How about that?

12:27.333 --> 12:28.532
You know,

12:28.533 --> 12:30.266
my dance card's full this week,

12:30.267 --> 12:32.299
but I can take your food order.

12:32.300 --> 12:33.966
Oh...

12:33.967 --> 12:36.199
Well, I guess I'll just have to

12:36.200 --> 12:39.100
give this menu another look, then.

12:40.533 --> 12:41.832
[both chuckling]

12:41.833 --> 12:44.033
Oops.
Sorry about that.

12:49.933 --> 12:51.099
That's very kind of you.

12:51.100 --> 12:52.532
That's the least I could do.

12:52.533 --> 12:54.232
Would you mind getting
my lady friend here

12:54.233 --> 12:55.766
one more steak,
when you get a chance?

12:55.767 --> 12:58.199
She has worked up
quite an appetite.

12:58.200 --> 12:59.466
Sure thing.

12:59.467 --> 13:01.132
Just let me clean this up.

13:01.133 --> 13:02.767
Of course.

13:05.400 --> 13:07.966
And could you go ahead
and make that real rare?

13:07.967 --> 13:10.099
'Cause she likes it bloody

13:10.100 --> 13:12.566
and bitin' back.

13:12.567 --> 13:13.967
[pats booth]

13:19.033 --> 13:22.000
[police sirens wailing]

13:29.067 --> 13:33.566
[gravel crunching]

13:33.567 --> 13:36.533
[engine puttering]

13:38.100 --> 13:39.767
Oh...

13:44.033 --> 13:45.532
Nobody come in,

13:45.533 --> 13:47.199
'cause I'm taking a bubble bath.

13:47.200 --> 13:49.100
I'm gonna hose off my coin purse.

13:52.633 --> 13:54.599
Surprisingly big dick.

13:54.600 --> 13:57.132
[both laughing]

13:57.133 --> 14:00.166
I hope all this celebration
means you found something.

14:00.167 --> 14:02.199
[glass clinking]

14:02.200 --> 14:03.400
Well...

14:07.400 --> 14:09.266
Come on inside.

14:09.267 --> 14:11.066
I made dinner.

14:11.067 --> 14:13.033
Tell all about it.

14:22.733 --> 14:25.566
My feet are killin' me.

14:25.567 --> 14:27.199
Just in time.

14:27.200 --> 14:29.399
Green beans
in a garlic-chili sauce.

14:29.400 --> 14:30.832
I hope it's not too spicy.

14:30.833 --> 14:34.999
Ain't no such thing
as too spicy.

14:35.000 --> 14:37.066
It's tofu.
You ever try it?

14:37.067 --> 14:38.399
No.

14:38.400 --> 14:40.132
Howard's a vegetarian.

14:40.133 --> 14:41.366
That right?
[chuckles]

14:41.367 --> 14:42.699
I didn't see that coming.

14:42.700 --> 14:44.500
It's a personal choice.

14:50.233 --> 14:52.332
Do you like it?

14:52.333 --> 14:54.399
- Hap?
- Hmm?

14:54.400 --> 14:56.066
- The food.
- Oh, yeah.

14:56.067 --> 14:58.866
- Do you like it?
- For beans.

14:58.867 --> 15:02.532
So, uh, how about

15:02.533 --> 15:04.699
you fill us in
on your progress today?

15:04.700 --> 15:06.667
Hmm, well, uh...

15:08.367 --> 15:10.766
I wouldn't call it definitive.

15:10.767 --> 15:12.299
You wouldn't?

15:12.300 --> 15:14.632
No, it's more complicated.

15:14.633 --> 15:15.733
Oh.

15:16.900 --> 15:20.099
We found the road in,

15:20.100 --> 15:21.832
leading to the bridge.

15:21.833 --> 15:23.399
Well, hey...

15:23.400 --> 15:25.399
Well, that sounds hopeful.

15:25.400 --> 15:26.966
It's pretty overgrown in there,

15:26.967 --> 15:28.466
and the old trails are gone.

15:28.467 --> 15:30.899
I'm pretty positive

15:30.900 --> 15:33.566
that we're in the right area.

15:33.567 --> 15:36.199
- You're pretty positive.
- Mm-hmm.

15:36.200 --> 15:38.432
Well, that's very encouraging,
isn't it, Trudy?

15:38.433 --> 15:40.199
Yeah, we'll go back
out there tomorrow,

15:40.200 --> 15:43.433
but like I said,
the trails are old.

15:45.100 --> 15:48.332
You guys had a big
adventure today, huh?

15:48.333 --> 15:50.632
- Just no bridge.
- Hmm.

15:50.633 --> 15:53.832
I can't say I'm not
disappointed, after Trudy's

15:53.833 --> 15:55.499
enthusiastic endorsement

15:55.500 --> 15:57.266
that you would be the one
to find it.

15:57.267 --> 15:59.432
Howard, give him a break.
It's the first day.

15:59.433 --> 16:00.932
I'll find it.

16:00.933 --> 16:02.766
It's gonna be a little

16:02.767 --> 16:04.332
harder than I thought.

16:04.333 --> 16:06.032
I mean, I'd hate
to see you let her down.

16:06.033 --> 16:07.732
I mean, she thinks

16:07.733 --> 16:08.866
so highly of you.

16:08.867 --> 16:11.166
Trudy's taste in men

16:11.167 --> 16:13.333
has always been questionable.

16:16.133 --> 16:17.932
Maybe I should leave,

16:17.933 --> 16:20.766
so you two can put
your dicks on the table,

16:20.767 --> 16:22.399
next to them toothpicks.

16:22.400 --> 16:25.000
- [laughing]
- Ooh...

16:26.933 --> 16:28.866
[chuckles]
She's right.

16:28.867 --> 16:30.066
We're a team,

16:30.067 --> 16:32.399
and we should act like one.

16:32.400 --> 16:35.366
You don't find it,
you don't find it.

16:35.367 --> 16:38.332
You go home, we keep trying,

16:38.333 --> 16:40.866
because it's a matter
of dedication.

16:40.867 --> 16:42.333
Isn't it?

16:57.667 --> 17:02.566
Chub, you're done eating.

17:02.567 --> 17:05.965
Let's walk the perimeter.

17:05.967 --> 17:08.398
I'll go with you.

17:08.400 --> 17:10.566
What's the odds
I'll find me a cheeseburger

17:10.567 --> 17:12.367
out there?

17:16.733 --> 17:18.233
[chuckles]

17:21.267 --> 17:22.900
[screen door slams shut]

17:25.800 --> 17:28.932
Charming.

17:28.933 --> 17:30.899
I can see why you married him.

17:30.900 --> 17:33.166
I also divorced him.

17:33.167 --> 17:35.799
It's my curse.

17:35.800 --> 17:38.966
They can't all be you.

17:38.967 --> 17:40.799
But he gets things done.

17:40.800 --> 17:44.766
Of course he does,
'cause he's got...

17:44.767 --> 17:47.366
What was that word he used?

17:47.367 --> 17:49.232
Dedication.

17:49.233 --> 17:51.766
That's a good thing.

17:51.767 --> 17:54.732
Leonard's rubbing off on you.

17:54.733 --> 17:57.433
He sees the world
through dirty glasses.

18:00.200 --> 18:03.366
Maybe the world is dirty.

18:03.367 --> 18:04.632
Well...

18:04.633 --> 18:07.232
a little optimism never hurt.

18:07.233 --> 18:10.166
<i>[solemn piano music]</i>

18:10.167 --> 18:18.167
<i>♪ ♪</i>

18:34.500 --> 18:36.466
[cat meows]

18:36.467 --> 18:38.532
<i>[bottles clattering]</i>

18:38.533 --> 18:41.499
<i>[hip-hop music playing]</i>

18:41.500 --> 18:43.499
<i>♪ ♪</i>

18:43.500 --> 18:46.666
<i>[dog barking]</i>

18:46.667 --> 18:48.299
<i>[over radio]
"Radio Mystery Hour"</i>

18:48.300 --> 18:50.799
<i>and a new
Sherlock Holmes adventure.</i>

18:50.800 --> 18:53.966
<i>And what new adventure
are we to embark on tonight?</i>

18:53.967 --> 18:55.799
<i>A macabre little escapade</i>

18:55.800 --> 18:57.366
<i>from Holmes' and my early years</i>

18:57.367 --> 19:01.166
<i>entitled
"The Dorchester Demon."</i>

19:01.167 --> 19:03.432
<i>It was in the year of 1887.</i>

19:03.433 --> 19:05.199
<i>Holmes and I were retiring</i>

19:05.200 --> 19:08.299
<i>before the fire when he began...</i>

19:08.300 --> 19:10.166
<i>"My dear fellow,</i>

19:10.167 --> 19:11.966
<i>"life is infinitely stranger</i>

19:11.967 --> 19:14.899
<i>"than anything which
the mind of man could invent.</i>

19:14.900 --> 19:18.566
<i>"Here, an example
from today's paper--</i>

19:18.567 --> 19:21.999
<i>"a husband's cruelty to his wife.</i>

19:22.000 --> 19:23.699
<i>"There's half a column of print,</i>

19:23.700 --> 19:25.399
<i>"but I know without reading it</i>

19:25.400 --> 19:27.832
<i>"that it is all
perfectly familiar to me.</i>

19:27.833 --> 19:30.966
<i>"There is, of course,
the other woman,</i>

19:30.967 --> 19:34.499
<i>"the drink, the push,
the blow, the bruise,</i>

19:34.500 --> 19:36.566
<i>"the sympathetic sister
or landlady.</i>

19:36.567 --> 19:38.832
<i>"The crudest of writers</i>

19:38.833 --> 19:40.832
<i>could invent
nothing more crude."</i>

19:40.833 --> 19:42.566
<i>Indeed, your example</i>

19:42.567 --> 19:44.366
<i>is an unfortunate one
for your argument...</i>

19:44.367 --> 19:47.532
[labored breathing]

19:47.533 --> 19:49.599
[panting]

19:49.600 --> 19:52.166
[glass shatters]

19:52.167 --> 19:54.666
<i>The husband was a teetotaler,</i>

19:54.667 --> 19:57.366
<i>and the conduct complained of</i>

19:57.367 --> 19:58.966
<i>was that he had drifted
into the habit of</i>

19:58.967 --> 20:00.766
<i>winding up every meal
by taking out</i>

20:00.767 --> 20:02.866
<i>his false teeth
and hurling them at his wife...</i>

20:02.867 --> 20:04.932
<i>I'm really starting
to like these people.</i>

20:04.933 --> 20:06.966
I hope they invite us
back next year.

20:06.967 --> 20:08.532
Yeah.
[chuckles]

20:08.533 --> 20:11.299
It's pretty obvious
they like you too.

20:11.300 --> 20:14.566
I think that Paco's
got a thing for you.

20:14.567 --> 20:15.766
[laughs]

20:15.767 --> 20:17.099
Maybe you won't go home

20:17.100 --> 20:18.999
empty-handed from here
after all.

20:19.000 --> 20:22.266
Oh, yeah,
his beauty's on the inside.

20:22.267 --> 20:24.067
[chuckles]

20:26.433 --> 20:30.432
See anything out there
today looked familiar?

20:30.433 --> 20:32.532
Maybe the road in does,

20:32.533 --> 20:36.699
but after that, could be on Venus.

20:36.700 --> 20:38.066
It's a friggin' river.

20:38.067 --> 20:40.299
Uh-uh.
Not a river.

20:40.300 --> 20:42.366
It's a tributary to a river.

20:42.367 --> 20:45.367
That's why Howard
couldn't find it.

20:47.833 --> 20:51.067
Well, aren't you the clever one?

20:53.400 --> 20:56.066
Son of a bitch can cook, though.

20:56.067 --> 21:00.599
Them string beans was good.
[sighs]

21:00.600 --> 21:02.232
Hmm.

21:02.233 --> 21:05.267
[sighs]

21:07.967 --> 21:10.899
<i>[rock music]</i>

21:10.900 --> 21:18.799
<i>♪ ♪</i>

21:18.800 --> 21:21.800
[air hissing]

21:31.267 --> 21:33.100
[engine revs]

21:52.000 --> 22:00.067
<i>♪ ♪</i>

22:14.400 --> 22:17.266
Been chopping for hours now.

22:17.267 --> 22:18.732
Where the hell we at, Hap?

22:18.733 --> 22:22.032
All I see is swamp.

22:22.033 --> 22:24.999
Talk a good game back home.

22:25.000 --> 22:27.432
Even had me fooled.

22:27.433 --> 22:28.999
Ain't nobody tell me

22:29.000 --> 22:30.866
I was gonna be on
a redneck safari and shit,

22:30.867 --> 22:32.599
sleeping on the floor,

22:32.600 --> 22:34.632
hanging out with the last
of the flower children.

22:34.633 --> 22:37.032
Damn tacos done took our job
at the rose field.

22:37.033 --> 22:38.599
We ain't got squat.

22:38.600 --> 22:39.932
Next thing you know,
we gonna be working

22:39.933 --> 22:41.733
at the McDonald's.

22:44.733 --> 22:46.499
What you smiling at?

22:46.500 --> 22:49.899
You either remember somethin',
or you farted.

22:49.900 --> 22:52.799
Don't tell me you farted.

22:52.800 --> 22:55.666
We used to dig
for night crawlers

22:55.667 --> 22:57.632
underneath that tree,

22:57.633 --> 23:01.532
so gonna be an old sign
over there,

23:01.533 --> 23:06.332
which means the iron bridge...

23:06.333 --> 23:08.432
is right here.

23:08.433 --> 23:11.599
[chuckles]

23:11.600 --> 23:14.633
[laughs]

23:21.000 --> 23:22.632
I told you.

23:22.633 --> 23:25.832
<i>[mellow rock music]</i>

23:25.833 --> 23:28.800
Didn't I tell you?

23:31.000 --> 23:33.933
Then where's the goddamn river?

23:43.633 --> 23:47.632
<i>Here you go, fellas, two more.</i>

23:47.633 --> 23:49.199
<i>[country rock music playing]</i>

23:49.200 --> 23:52.632
<i>[pool balls striking]</i>

23:52.633 --> 23:57.832
How does a river just disappear?

23:57.833 --> 24:00.399
May be the wrong bridge.

24:00.400 --> 24:03.366
No, no, it's the right bridge.

24:03.367 --> 24:05.233
I know that much.

24:07.300 --> 24:11.432
Probably some old, made-up,
bullshit prison story anyway.

24:11.433 --> 24:15.566
This Softboy guy--
probably pulling Howard's crank.

24:15.567 --> 24:17.666
Trudy bought it.

24:17.667 --> 24:20.633
Of course you bought it.

24:22.700 --> 24:27.132
If you believe that,
then why are you here?

24:27.133 --> 24:30.599
I'm here watchin' your ass.

24:30.600 --> 24:32.932
Since when did my ass
need watchin'?

24:32.933 --> 24:35.232
Since always.

24:35.233 --> 24:36.766
You act like it's the first time

24:36.767 --> 24:38.166
I had to pull it out the fire.

24:38.167 --> 24:41.200
Hell, I need oven mitts
just to hang out with you.

24:46.233 --> 24:48.633
Then don't.

24:50.633 --> 24:53.600
'Cause I don't need a babysitter.

24:57.200 --> 24:59.799
You know what
the real question is?

24:59.800 --> 25:02.100
What are you doing here?

25:16.100 --> 25:24.100
<i>♪ ♪</i>

25:55.400 --> 25:57.366
[sighs]

25:57.367 --> 26:00.532
What's up?

26:00.533 --> 26:03.500
Chester.

26:05.900 --> 26:08.399
Got to go back.

26:08.400 --> 26:10.399
Hmm.

26:10.400 --> 26:13.366
<i>[solemn music]</i>

26:13.367 --> 26:21.367
<i>♪ ♪</i>

26:36.267 --> 26:38.432
Leonard.

26:38.433 --> 26:41.866
Yeah?

26:41.867 --> 26:44.433
I'm really sorry
to hear about your uncle.

26:47.400 --> 26:48.699
He's old.

26:48.700 --> 26:51.032
Shit happens.

26:51.033 --> 26:54.367
Still, it's got to be tough.

26:58.533 --> 27:00.166
You take care of him

27:00.167 --> 27:01.932
while I'm gone, now, won't you?

27:01.933 --> 27:04.866
He's a grown man, last I looked.

27:04.867 --> 27:07.866
More like a puppy dog.

27:07.867 --> 27:09.866
Loves unconditionally.

27:09.867 --> 27:12.266
You just the ball he keeps
chasing into the street.

27:12.267 --> 27:15.132
Don't let him be roadkill.

27:15.133 --> 27:17.066
I'll make sure he gets his shots

27:17.067 --> 27:19.200
and give him a bath
before I give him back.

27:21.333 --> 27:22.966
It's sweet, actually,

27:22.967 --> 27:26.133
the way you pretend he needs you.

27:29.933 --> 27:31.666
[footsteps thudding, door slams]

27:31.667 --> 27:33.132
Hey, uh,

27:33.133 --> 27:36.799
this is for gas.

27:36.800 --> 27:38.832
You been holding out on me.

27:38.833 --> 27:43.332
Look, we're still partners.

27:43.333 --> 27:46.566
Whether you're here or not
when we find it,

27:46.567 --> 27:48.099
you still get your share.

27:48.100 --> 27:49.732
I ain't gonna hold my breath.

27:49.733 --> 27:52.999
Hmm...
[chuckles]

27:53.000 --> 27:54.599
Hey.

27:54.600 --> 27:58.532
Come on, man!

27:58.533 --> 28:00.366
That's why dudes
don't hug each other.

28:00.367 --> 28:02.567
Yeah, sorry.

28:03.867 --> 28:06.967
Trudy, remember what I said.

28:13.333 --> 28:15.333
[engine turns over]

28:23.333 --> 28:25.332
What'd he say?

28:25.333 --> 28:29.232
Nothin'.

28:29.233 --> 28:30.499
Oh.

28:30.500 --> 28:33.499
<i>[country music playing]</i>

28:33.500 --> 28:38.299
<i>♪ ♪</i>

28:38.300 --> 28:42.332
<i>♪ I walk along ♪</i>

28:42.333 --> 28:47.032
<i>♪ The crowded street ♪</i>

28:47.033 --> 28:50.399
<i>♪ Afraid your friends ♪</i>

28:50.400 --> 28:55.366
<i>♪ I'll chance to meet ♪</i>

28:55.367 --> 28:58.666
<i>♪ They know that I ♪</i>

28:58.667 --> 29:03.766
<i>♪ Have caused you pain ♪</i>

29:03.767 --> 29:06.532
<i>♪ All I can do ♪</i>

29:06.533 --> 29:10.899
<i>♪ Is hang my head in shame ♪</i>

29:10.900 --> 29:17.232
<i>♪ ♪</i>

29:17.233 --> 29:20.232
[elevator dings]

29:20.233 --> 29:24.132
<i>[over PA]
Dr. McAllister, 472.</i>

29:24.133 --> 29:27.032
<i>Dr. McAllister, 472, please.</i>

29:27.033 --> 29:28.532
Chester Pine?

29:28.533 --> 29:30.532
Hmm? Good?

29:30.533 --> 29:33.566
Huh, Chester?

29:33.567 --> 29:35.400
Okay.

29:44.600 --> 29:46.200
Is it bad?

29:48.467 --> 29:50.799
He's pretty out of it.

29:50.800 --> 29:53.533
They got him on some heavy drugs.

29:58.800 --> 30:01.932
I'm gonna leave you alone
with him.

30:01.933 --> 30:05.199
<i>[over PA] Mrs. Wayman,
can you come to admitting?</i>

30:05.200 --> 30:08.200
<i>Mrs. Wayman,
come to admitting, please.</i>

30:21.100 --> 30:23.132
[gurney rattling]

30:23.133 --> 30:26.066
<i>[solemn music]</i>

30:26.067 --> 30:34.067
<i>♪ ♪</i>

31:04.967 --> 31:08.499
<i>[blows landing]</i>

31:08.500 --> 31:16.500
<i>♪ ♪</i>

31:21.467 --> 31:24.499
[breathing heavily]

31:24.500 --> 31:27.467
[grunting]

31:34.600 --> 31:37.600
[panting]

31:55.433 --> 31:59.500
[crickets chirping]

32:09.667 --> 32:11.499
[sighs]

32:11.500 --> 32:13.866
Hey, cowboy.

32:13.867 --> 32:15.532
Wanna take a ride?

32:15.533 --> 32:17.632
Leonard took our horse.

32:17.633 --> 32:19.499
[keys jingle]

32:19.500 --> 32:20.632
Howard's Saab.

32:20.633 --> 32:22.399
Still got a copy of the keys.

32:22.400 --> 32:24.066
Will he mind?

32:24.067 --> 32:27.000
Of course.

32:32.733 --> 32:35.533
Thank you.

32:51.900 --> 32:53.799
Got these for your
birthday last year,

32:53.800 --> 32:55.732
before we split up.

32:55.733 --> 32:58.499
You might as well have them.

32:58.500 --> 33:00.400
Happy birthday.

33:03.300 --> 33:04.432
How's Hap?

33:04.433 --> 33:07.467
He's good.

33:10.133 --> 33:11.367
And Switch?

33:13.500 --> 33:17.032
There's a little white hair
in his face.

33:17.033 --> 33:18.932
Guess we all gettin' older.

33:18.933 --> 33:20.532
Not me, honey.

33:20.533 --> 33:22.667
I refuse.

33:29.400 --> 33:32.199
<i>[country melody playing]</i>

33:32.200 --> 33:34.966
[sighs]

33:34.967 --> 33:39.199
<i>♪ ♪</i>

33:39.200 --> 33:43.599
<i>♪ If ever you decide ♪</i>

33:43.600 --> 33:48.699
<i>♪ That you want me ♪</i>

33:48.700 --> 33:52.532
<i>♪ If ever you decide ♪</i>

33:52.533 --> 33:56.799
<i>♪ That you care ♪</i>

33:56.800 --> 33:59.566
<i>♪ Well, I'll tell you ♪</i>

33:59.567 --> 34:05.132
<i>♪ Where you can find me ♪</i>

34:05.133 --> 34:07.532
<i>♪ It's in the middle ♪</i>

34:07.533 --> 34:10.032
<i>♪ Yes, in the middle ♪</i>

34:10.033 --> 34:14.532
<i>♪ Of nowhere ♪</i>

34:14.533 --> 34:19.166
<i>♪ Yes, I'm in the middle ♪</i>

34:19.167 --> 34:23.831
<i>♪ Of nowhere ♪</i>

34:23.833 --> 34:28.032
<i>♪ And that's just the way ♪</i>

34:28.033 --> 34:32.498
<i>♪ That I feel ♪</i>

34:32.500 --> 34:35.065
<i>♪ I know ♪</i>

34:35.067 --> 34:38.931
♪<i> There's no tomorrow ♪</i>

34:38.933 --> 34:41.466
We got married on that porch.

34:41.467 --> 34:45.167
You had hair down
to your shoulders.

34:47.300 --> 34:49.232
That silly peasant shirt

34:49.233 --> 34:52.266
you sewed flowers on.

34:53.766 --> 34:55.299
I screwed up, Hap.

34:55.300 --> 34:58.099
Oh, come on,
it wasn't that silly.

34:58.100 --> 35:02.799
I mean it.
In life.

35:02.800 --> 35:04.732
I'm not perfect.

35:04.733 --> 35:08.066
No.
Mm...

35:08.067 --> 35:10.232
No one said you had to be.

35:10.233 --> 35:13.766
<i>♪ That you just don't care ♪</i>

35:13.767 --> 35:16.666
A phone call would've been nice.

35:16.667 --> 35:19.132
<i>♪ I know ♪</i>

35:19.133 --> 35:23.632
<i>♪ There's no tomorrow ♪</i>

35:23.633 --> 35:27.366
I miss the way you used to be.

35:27.367 --> 35:29.566
Always the noble one,

35:29.567 --> 35:32.866
ready to make a stand.

35:32.867 --> 35:35.999
And now?

35:36.000 --> 35:39.866
You just seem sad.

35:39.867 --> 35:41.666
Like you missed your
chance at the ring.

35:41.667 --> 35:44.066
[sighs]

35:44.067 --> 35:47.532
<i>♪ And that's
just the way I feel ♪</i>

35:47.533 --> 35:49.566
But if I'm right,

35:49.567 --> 35:52.099
I think I can cheer you up.

35:52.100 --> 35:55.099
Bring back a little
of that old Hap.

35:55.100 --> 35:57.266
Right about what?

35:57.267 --> 36:01.232
You'll see.

36:01.233 --> 36:04.466
<i>♪ Yes, in the middle ♪</i>

36:04.467 --> 36:10.299
<i>♪ Of nowhere ♪</i>

36:10.300 --> 36:13.899
<i>♪ Each time I tell you ♪</i>

36:13.900 --> 36:15.932
♪<i> That I love you ♪</i>

36:15.933 --> 36:18.366
[passionate moaning]

36:18.367 --> 36:22.599
<i>♪ You tell me that you ♪</i>

36:22.600 --> 36:25.433
<i>♪ Just don't care ♪</i>

36:32.300 --> 36:33.699
Well, hot damn.

36:33.700 --> 36:35.099
If it isn't the river.

36:35.100 --> 36:36.966
So this is what I found out.

36:36.967 --> 36:39.032
Howard did his research,
all right,

36:39.033 --> 36:41.866
but he missed one important thing.

36:41.867 --> 36:42.932
What?

36:42.933 --> 36:44.466
Enough time goes by,

36:44.467 --> 36:45.833
things change.

36:46.967 --> 36:49.967
Look.

36:52.433 --> 36:54.466
- Here's your bridge.
- Mm-hmm.

36:54.467 --> 36:56.499
Here's your tributary,
where it should be...

36:56.500 --> 36:57.832
Okay.

36:57.833 --> 36:59.799
And here's what Howard missed.

36:59.800 --> 37:02.232
20 years ago, the Sabine flooded,

37:02.233 --> 37:04.299
along with half the county,

37:04.300 --> 37:07.966
so severe it rearranged
the river itself,

37:07.967 --> 37:10.932
so the tributaries all shifted,

37:10.933 --> 37:13.533
and a new river was created.

37:16.567 --> 37:20.567
So that's why the bridge
was over a dry gulch.

37:21.967 --> 37:24.999
How'd you know all this?
Library?

37:25.000 --> 37:26.533
Bait shop.

37:30.333 --> 37:32.399
That car could be anywhere.

37:32.400 --> 37:35.932
Nope. The flood stopped
at the Old Mill Dam.

37:35.933 --> 37:38.199
So there's a good chance
that car's between the dry gulch

37:38.200 --> 37:39.932
and in front of that dam.

37:39.933 --> 37:42.166
That's less than
a half mile to search.

37:42.167 --> 37:44.599
Sounds ambitious.

37:44.600 --> 37:47.832
A little ambition
goes a long way.

37:47.833 --> 37:50.066
You told me that once.

37:50.067 --> 37:51.699
I did?

37:51.700 --> 37:53.233
Yes, sir.

37:55.133 --> 37:56.533
Now blow that up.

37:58.267 --> 38:00.299
We're gonna do
a little night fishing.

38:00.300 --> 38:01.833
[chuckles]

38:05.667 --> 38:09.666
<i>[quiet piano music]</i>

38:09.667 --> 38:17.633
<i>♪ ♪</i>

38:22.700 --> 38:24.266
Trudy?

38:24.267 --> 38:32.267
<i>♪ ♪</i>

38:56.233 --> 38:59.233
[flare hissing]

39:03.900 --> 39:05.532
It's here, Hap.

39:05.533 --> 39:06.833
I can feel it.

39:09.767 --> 39:11.566
How do you do that?

39:11.567 --> 39:13.432
What?

39:13.433 --> 39:15.967
Stay so hopeful.

39:18.833 --> 39:20.466
You really just gonna
take your money

39:20.467 --> 39:22.899
and go when this is over?

39:22.900 --> 39:24.733
That's your plan, huh?

39:26.100 --> 39:27.733
You could come with me.

39:32.767 --> 39:36.299
I'm sorry, Trudy.

39:36.300 --> 39:40.099
I'm just not interested
in the downtrodden anymore.

39:40.100 --> 39:43.400
Hell, I'm one of 'em.

39:45.100 --> 39:46.900
I feel sorry for you, Hap.

39:49.600 --> 39:52.599
You got nothing left inside
to hold the dark away.

39:52.600 --> 39:55.567
Yeah?
Like what?

39:58.967 --> 40:02.133
Howard and I were
in Mexico about a year ago...

40:03.500 --> 40:05.432
At this small orphanage,

40:05.433 --> 40:08.066
just an old monastery,

40:08.067 --> 40:09.433
bunch of nuns...

40:10.867 --> 40:15.366
And all these children.

40:15.367 --> 40:18.832
Dirt poor, hungry,

40:18.833 --> 40:22.299
some of them sick,

40:22.300 --> 40:25.099
yet they were still happy.

40:25.100 --> 40:27.133
They had faith
in something greater.

40:29.367 --> 40:30.766
And?

40:30.767 --> 40:34.699
I promised myself that one day,

40:34.700 --> 40:38.299
I'd go back and change the world
for those children.

40:38.300 --> 40:40.167
That's what keeps me going.

40:43.367 --> 40:45.332
Bet you think that's silly,
don't you?

40:45.333 --> 40:46.333
No.

40:48.367 --> 40:49.767
No, I don't.

40:51.567 --> 40:53.500
[water gurgles]

40:58.100 --> 41:00.367
Hey, b-back up here.
Back up, back up.

41:02.367 --> 41:04.000
I think I got something here.

41:07.067 --> 41:08.932
[reel clicking]
Oh!

41:08.933 --> 41:10.400
[reel clicking]

41:21.100 --> 41:22.533
Give me the line,
give me the line.

41:33.033 --> 41:34.367
Oh, my God.

41:35.600 --> 41:36.999
We found it!

41:37.000 --> 41:39.366
- Hap, you found it.
- Oh! We found it!

41:39.367 --> 41:41.166
[both laugh]

41:41.167 --> 41:44.132
- Ah!
- [screams]

41:44.133 --> 41:46.232
[screams] Hap!

41:46.233 --> 41:47.466
[alligator growls]

41:47.467 --> 41:49.132
- Hey, let go.
- [screaming]

41:49.133 --> 41:50.632
- Breathe, breathe, come on!
- [screaming]

41:50.633 --> 41:52.566
[screaming]
- I got you, I got you.

41:52.567 --> 41:54.799
[screaming]

41:54.800 --> 41:56.166
Swim!

41:56.167 --> 41:59.032
Swim to the side,
swim to the side!

41:59.033 --> 42:02.066
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

42:02.067 --> 42:08.666
<i>♪ ♪</i>

42:08.667 --> 42:10.767
Let's go.
Come on, out of the water!

42:11.900 --> 42:14.332
[panicked breathing]

42:14.333 --> 42:15.966
Oh, God!
[crying]

42:15.967 --> 42:18.966
Hey, hey, it's okay.

42:18.967 --> 42:22.266
It's gone, it's gone.
We're safe.

42:22.267 --> 42:24.533
Hey, Trudy...

42:32.433 --> 42:35.432
<i>[gentle guitar music]</i>

42:35.433 --> 42:43.400
<i>♪ ♪</i>

42:59.700 --> 43:01.467
[gasps]

43:19.033 --> 43:21.967
[both panting]

43:24.700 --> 43:25.967
Oh, God.

43:28.500 --> 43:29.933
[cries out]

43:40.833 --> 43:48.833
<i>♪ ♪</i>

43:55.133 --> 43:57.499
Hap...

43:57.500 --> 43:59.433
Yeah, I know.

44:05.500 --> 44:07.367
I know.

